The paper deals with optimization problems on graphs, specifically finding large induced subgraphs with certain properties. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of Counting Monadic Second Order Logic (CMSO) also suggests a connection to logic and computation (cs.LG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper presents an algorithmic meta-theorem, which could be of interest to the computational complexity community (cs.CC).
